  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Several evidences in the literature suggest sleep interruption in critical care patients.
      Nowadays, the amount and the quality of sleep phases during the length of stay in the
      intensive care unit are largely unknown.

      In this study, the amount of time spent by the patients in N1, N2 N3 and REM phases during
      sleep is quantified.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
